			<ns0:name>halya...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112856509894568708731/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Deadlock scenario:
1. Debug stub thread locks target-&amp;gt;mutex_ in debug stub loop (Target::Run).
2. NaCl thread exits and locks nap-&amp;gt;thread_mu in NaClAppThreadTeardown.
3. Debug stub thread executes Target::SuspendAllThreads which calls NaClUntrustedThreadsSuspendAll. The last function waits on nap-&amp;gt;thread_mu.
4. NaCl thread calls debug_stub_callbacks-&amp;gt;thread_exit_hook which calls Target::IgnoreThreads. The last function waits on target-&amp;gt;mutex_.

The deadlock was introduced in revision 10415, https://codereview.chromium.org/11471038 while fixing a different bug.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-12-24T11:07:35.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-12-20T10:56:15.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
